Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Rene Ceasar Williams

records.descr: DE not competent to stand trial, case suspended

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Rene Ceasar Williams appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Connor Romenesko in court for Rene Ceasar Williams.  Attorney Amanda Korin Kirklewski in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for a competency hearing.  Sworn for the State: Doctor Jenna Goebel (Examining Psychologist).  It is the opinion of Doctor Goebel that Mr. Williams is NOT competent to proceed and more likely than not to regain competency within the statutory timeframe.  Closing arguments heard.  

Court adopts the Doctor's findings and suspends the proceedings.  Court ordered Mr. Williams COMMITTED for treatment.  Order of Commitment for Treatment signed and filed by the Court.  Court scheduled a Doctor's Report Return.  Case adjourned to Branch 2, Rm 635 CH.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for January 30, 2023 at 08:30 am.
Signed and filed: Order of Commitment for Treatment (Incompetency)
Received and Filed: Proposed Order of Commitment for Treatment (Incompetency)

Defendant Rene Ceasar Williams not in court, in custody, refused to be produced.  Attorney Connor Romenesko in court for Rene Ceasar Williams.  Prosecuting attorney Sarah Dahdouh in court for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for return on doctors report.  State does not dispute the findings, however the defense contests the report.   Case adjourned for contested doctors report hearing.
Competency hearing scheduled for October 28, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant Rene Ceasar Williams not in court, in custody.  Attorney Connor Romenesko in court for Rene Ceasar Williams.  Prosecuting attorney Sarah Dahdouh in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a return on doctor's report. No report has been filed with the court. Defense counsel recently retained. Discussion held. Defendant has a felony matter in Branch 2 and will be seeking a global offer and requests the court to authorize transfer. Court authorizes transfer to Branch 2 for purposes of a global resolution, if accepted. Case adjourned to Br. 30.
Status conference scheduled for September 20, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Richards, Branch 30.   Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for September 12, 2022 at 08:30 am.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE BENCH  WARRANT.

Attorney Douglas J. Rebholz in court.  Erika Strebel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a Bench Warrant to be issued REMAND TO COMMISSIONER.  Court takes no action as to bail.

Attorney Douglas J. Rebholz in court.  Navjot Singh Hira appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case set for pre-trial conference.  No appearance by the defendant.  Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed until the next court date.  Case adjourned to Br. 30.  Calendar call scheduled for June 30, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered no contact with W.C and M.M
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered Justice Point Pretrial Services LEVEL 1 SUPERVISION.  Court reminders.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Rene Ceasar Williams in court with attorney Corey R. Flynn.  Defendant Rene Ceasar Williams in custody.  Matthew Richard Westphal appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Rene Ceasar Williams appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Richards, Branch 30.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.
